  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (903a073 2022-11-14T00:07:04.292547Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nRun both tests below separately.\r\n\r\n* With `forge test --mt test_wrong_balance -vv`, the balance after the revert is wrong\r\n* With `forge test --mt test_panic`, forge panics\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.13;\r\n\r\nimport \"forge-std/Test.sol\";\r\nimport \"../src/Counter.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract CounterTest is Test {\r\n    Counter public counter;\r\n    Actor a;\r\n    Actor b;\r\n\r\n    function setUp() public {\r\n        a = new Actor();\r\n        b = new Actor();\r\n        vm.deal(address(a), 1 ether);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    // should not end up with 0 balance\r\n    function test_wrong_balance() public {\r\n        console.log(\"should be 1 ether       \",address(a).balance);\r\n        vm.expectRevert(bytes(\"rev\"));\r\n        a.spendFail(b);\r\n        console.log(\"should still be 1 ether \",address(a).balance);\r\n        a.spendSuccess(b); // panics here if back_and_forth() is called before\r\n    }\r\n    // panics\r\n    function test_panic() public {\r\n        back_and_forth();\r\n        test_wrong_balance();\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function back_and_forth() internal {\r\n        a.spendSuccess(b);\r\n        b.spendSuccess(a);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\ncontract Actor {\r\n    function spendSuccess(Actor a) public {\r\n        a.receiveSuccess{value: 1 ether}();\r\n        // note: if the line above is replaced by the line below, there is no panic\r\n        // payable(address(a)).transfer(1 ether);\r\n    }\r\n    function spendFail(Actor a) public {\r\n        a.receiveFail{value: 1 ether}();\r\n    }\r\n    function receiveFail() public payable {\r\n        revert(\"rev\");\r\n    }\r\n    function receiveSuccess() public payable {\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```",
